    "long_instructions": "## Computing Innovation Map\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/6f32ab87e5311ad41bebfe978ed14a71-image-1738282808454.png)\r\n\r\n**Need a refresher on key terms?**  \r\n- An **industry** is a group of businesses or organizations focused on a particular field (e.g., healthcare, agriculture, fashion).  \r\n- An **innovation** is a new idea, technology, or tool that improves how something is done in that industry.  \r\n- *Example:* In the healthcare industry, an innovation like smart prosthetics helps patients walk again using advanced sensors and software.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Do This:\r\n\r\n* Click the link to open the interactive Computing Innovation Map.\r\n* Click on the markers to explore different computing innovations in medicine, agriculture, education, and fashion.\r\n* Watch videos and read descriptions to learn how each innovation works.\r\n* Choose one innovation to investigate.\r\n\r\n**Note:** If you are unable to access the site linked below, you can use this resource as an alternative [Computing Innovation Map](https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/11_vTxAX7WZTmFqn2jQRvDkErAhHlQriLj2KfWEJM2Zg/edit?usp=sharing)",
